reviewText: DINOSAUR ISLAND is a Jim wynorski / Fred Olen Ray film. As such, it contains an island full of beautiful, boulder-breasted women, and a few dinosaurs wandering around. Plot? A plane carrying a group of soldiers crashes on the island of the title. While ogling the uber-babes, a giant, horribly-animated reptile attacks! After the big lizard runs off, the soldiers are captured by the island girls, who believe that one of them is their "savior", predicted by "the sacred scrolls". Then, it's off w/ the bikini tops and in for a swim! Next, it's into the stone-age hot tub! You get the idea. Toni Naples stars as Queen Morgana. Enjoy...

reviewText: I find it hard to believe that this truly, purposely funny ( very campy  ) movie is not available on DVD! It really does have some of the worst special effects ever, but who really cares about bad effects and lousy, cheap dinosaurs, when it offers some of the truly best B movie actresses ever! It's a classic DD, err I mean B, soft porn flick!! I'm a great fan of Michelle Bauer and go to great lengths to find her films!. Griffin Drew is way above average in every way, Nikki Fritz is always a presence,and Toni Naples , Becky Lebeau , and Antonia  Dorian truly roouunnndd out the fine Cast.If You like cute well rounded women running around half-naked for an hour and a half, ( This is what I bought it for and why love it! ) than you won't be disappointed. If you buy it thinking of Oscar movies, then save The Money to buy Dr.Zhivago. I love B and DD movies and this is one of my favorites. Net Flix carries a High Def copy of this for streaming. I wish they would make this this into a DVD !  They have high def copies of a lot of other crummy movies that I,d give anything to have on DVD.Bummer!!!

reviewText: Another low budget masterpiece.  What made this movie for me was the lead females, all very attractive, all very naked.  I first saw this as a young lad, and unable to find more graphic presentations of lovely women, I enjoyed this immensely.  There is some softcore sex though, so be warned.The plot isn't bad, and the acting is surpringly good.  The dinosaurs are thoroughly unconvincing, but who cares?  In movies like these, you've got to play along or why bother watching?It's not a great movie, but for what the cast and crew had to work with, it's a damn fine effort.  If you enjoy low budget cinema, I whole-heartedly recommend it.

reviewText: I viewed this because I LIKE Dinosaurs, monsters, etc. Ray Harryhausen it's not, but in it's own way, it's not that bad. I've seen TERRIBLE movies (In my opinion), that got better reviews than this one! (Attack of the Killer Tomatoes for instance. I would rate Tomatoes a -4 if it were possible!) This movie is WAY better! Amazonian Warrior Women, Mild Porn, (Bare Breasts), lots of comedy. Not the best F/X, but then again, not the worst, either. For example: The Dinosaur eating the wounded soldier; if a real Dinosaur ate in this fashion, it would most likely choke. (Somebody would have to perform the Heimlich Maneuver on it.) Overall, I found it amusing. (Not boring, not scary, not the best acting, but amusing. I'm going to look for the DVD to purchase.)

reviewText: This is a very cheesy film featuring soft core movie stars. The dinosaurs are as realistic as sock puppets and they make Gumby look human. American soldiers are stranded on an island inhabited by what appears to be a casting call for an Andy Sidoris film. The women are extremely beautiful and don't grow leg or armpit hair. They do bath topless and frolic in the water like girls at the Playboy mansion. They don't tan very well either.The bad news is that the guys must kill "The Great One" (not Jackie Gleason) a sock puppet version of T. Rex. Corney jokes and lines abound, nothing that is a knee slapper. Make no mistake, the nudity is the main attraction with a token cat fight.Parental guide: No f-bombs, sex, nudity (Antonia Dorian, Michelle Bauer, Griffin Drew, Toni Naples, Nikki Fritz, Becky LeBeau)
